{"title":"Updated Argon 18 Dark Matter gravel adventure bike gets 57mm tyre clearance and goes slacker","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/argon-18-dark-matter-2025","date":1745848800000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/argon-18-dark-matter-2025\">Updated Argon 18 Dark Matter gravel adventure bike gets 57mm tyre clearance and goes slacker</a></p>\n\n<p>Argon 18 has updated its Dark Matter gravel adventure bike, upping tyre clearance to 57mm and adding in-frame storage. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rather than a specialist<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-gravel-adventure-bikes\"> gravel adventure</a> or <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-gravel-race-bikes\">gravel race bike</a>, Argon 18 has aimed to make the Dark Matter an all-rounder, suitable for everything from fast gravel to bikepacking, so you get the full range of mounts, including fork leg mounts. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Argon 18 Dark Matter comes in three specs, with prices from £3,500 to £6,500 in the UK.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Longer geometry </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373A.3E.1old_34-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>Argon 18</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Canadian brand has tweaked the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-does-frame-geometry-affect-a-bike\">geometry </a>for the 2025 Dark Matter, with longer chainstays, probably needed anyway to accommodate those tyres, and a longer <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/what-is-a-bikes-wheelbase\">wheelbase</a>. The <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-to-measure-stack-and-reach\">reach </a>has also been extended and the stack increased. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The head tube angle is now 1° slacker – another gravel trend – and hovers around 70° while the frame weight has dropped by 100-150g, both dependent on frame size.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-gravel-adventure-bikes\">Best gravel adventure bikes 2025 reviewed</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/argon-18-sum-pro-review\">Argon 18 Sum Pro road bike review</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-gravel-bike\">The best gravel bikes 2025 reviewed for racing and adventure</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-to-measure-stack-and-reach\">Stack and reach explained: How to measure them and why they matter</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-does-frame-geometry-affect-a-bike\">How does frame geometry affect a road bike?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<p>Argon says that the bike is designed for<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/power-of-one-the-rise-of-the-1x-groupset\"> 1x drivetrains</a>, although you can also go 2x and add a suspension fork and a dropper post. There’s a T47 <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bottom-bracket-standards-guide\">bottom bracket</a> and Argon 18 fits a bash guard to the underside of the lower down tube.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Big tyre clearance is turning into the gravel theme for 2025. Already we’ve seen the Allied Able with 57mm, the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/ridley-ignite-gtx\">Ridley Ignite GTX</a> with 58mm and the niche <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/lee-cougan-super-gravel\">Lee Cougan Super Gravel</a> with 60mm clearance and full suspension. Front ends are also increasingly being configured so that you can swap in a suspension fork without compromising the bike’s geometry.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+4\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-970x300.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Argon 18 Dark Matter 2025 specs and prices</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"650\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373B.2E.1old_side-970x650.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373B.2E.1old_side-970x650.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373B.2E.1old_side-300x201.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373B.2E.1old_side-768x515.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373B.2E.1old_side-1536x1030.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373B.2E.1old_side-2048x1373.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373B.2E.1old_side-750x503.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Dark-Matter-DM.M.373B.2E.1old_side-1140x764.webp 1140w\" /><figcaption>Argon 18</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Argon 18 will sell the Dark Matter in three specs, all 1x. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Dark Matter SRAM Force XPLR AXS</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frame/fork:</strong> Dark Matter carbon</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Groupset:</strong> SRAM Force XPLR AXS Wide 40t, 10-44t</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wheelset:</strong> Zipp 303 XPLR S</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tyres:</strong> Schwalbe G-One RX Pro TLR 50mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bars:</strong> FSA A-Wing Pro AGX</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stem: </strong>FSA SMR-II</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Saddle:</strong> Repente Quasar 2.0</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Seatpost:</strong> Argon 18 TDS-C carbon</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> £6,500 / $6,650 / €7,395</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Dark Matter SRAM Rival AXS</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frame/fork:</strong> Dark Matter carbon</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Groupset:</strong> SRAM Rival XPLR AXS Wide 40t, 10-44t</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wheelset:</strong> DT Swiss G1800 alloy</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tyres:</strong> Schwalbe G-One RX Pro TLR 50mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bars:</strong> FSA A-Wing Pro AGX</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stem: </strong>FSA SMR-II</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Saddle:</strong> Repente Quasar 2.0</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Seatpost:</strong> Argon 18 TDS-C carbon</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> £4,500 / $4,650 / €5,095</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Dark Matter Shimano GRX</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frame/fork:</strong> Dark Matter carbon</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Groupset:</strong> Shimano GRX RX822/610 40t, 10-51t</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wheelset:</strong> DT Swiss G1800 alloy</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tyres:</strong> Vittoria Terreno T50 Mixed 50mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bars:</strong> FSA A-Wing Pro AGX</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stem: </strong>FSA SMR-II</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Saddle:</strong> Repente Quasar S 2.0</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Seatpost:</strong> Argon 18 TDS-C carbon</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> £3,500 / $3,650 / €3,995</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/argon-18-dark-matter-2025\">Updated Argon 18 Dark Matter gravel adventure bike gets 57mm tyre clearance and goes slacker</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Pnorman","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"ed0b044e67f505bf0a6038f2e9256d1535222dd952a17f07e116289031dc1263","category":"Cycling"}